zone_description: Marks a transition between steady accretion decreased rates of accertion
An area of shifting erosion and accretion, influenced by the shoreline armor at the entrance to North Bay, and defies broad characterization due to many environmental and manmade factors
Highly built environment, frequently nourished by the Army Corps of Engineers and influenced by sediment input and the Westport Jetty
Another dynamic environment, marked by shoreline development influencing wave action and sediment transport
Breakpoint between Westport and the highly dynamic zone at the entrance to Willapa Bay
Highly dynamic, highly volatile and uncertain area of rapid erosion at the south end of the entrance to Willapa Bay accompanied by rapid accretion to the north
Strong rates of accretion and buildout of beaches
Another small subreach of decreased rates of accretion, potentially influenced by the presence of a heavily used OBA near a suburb of Klipsan beach
Steady, relatively high levels of accertion present through this area
Small subreach of decreased accertion rates as erosion begins
Area of fluctuation but overall erosion, potentially stabilized by the North Head Lighthouse outcropping
Highly unstable area of strong erosion
